<div id="lists" class="cell markdown">
A bullet list opens right after a paragraph line, with no blank between:

* apples
* pears

An ordered list interrupts the same way:

# second
# third

A parenthesized or roman marker has a list shape but no enabled style here, so it breaks off as its own plain paragraph rather than folding in:

(5) parenthesized

A decimal marker closed by a single paren stays prose and folds in, so these two lines remain one paragraph: 1) not a list 2) still prose

</div>
